article.headline: Indiana St. 69, Texas-Pan American 46
article.story: CHICAGO -- Indiana State placed three players in double figures and shot 50 percent in a season-opening 69-46 rout of Texas-Pan American in the Nick Kladis Classic on Friday night. Jordan Printy scored five points during a 10-0 run that turned a 15-15 tie into a 25-15 Sycamores lead with 7:45 left in the first half. Indiana State led 38-20 at the half, and the lead never dipped below nine after that. Printy and Koang Doluony each hit three 3-pointers and scored 11 points to pace Indiana State. Jake Kelly added 10 points, and Carl Richard had a game-high 13 rebounds. Perry Petty's 11 points led Texas-Pan American, which shot only 24.5 percent and was outrebounded 38-26. The Sycamores won in the debut of head coach Greg Lansing. The meeting against Texas-Pan American was the first between the schools.
